The Judd or Magee Cemetery is located upon sections on South lines between section 18 and 19,
about 1 1/2 miles south of Wiota Cemetery.  The lot is bisected by a line fence between Clifford
Wright and Bruce Behrends' farms.  Very little of the cemetery still remains today.

Also known as the Benjamin Purcell Cemetery, Hodges Purcell is a small cemetery located in
Harrison County, Iowa.  There are only two known burials at this Cemetery; Orvil Hodges and
Benjamin Purcell. It is located on the bluff behind the farmhouse on the west side of Oneida
Avenue, between Easton Trail and 153rd Street.

Galland's Grove Cemetery is located in Garland's Grove in Shelby County, Iowa.  It is located 
just down the hill from Holcomb Cemetery.  It is an RLDS cemetery with only a handful of 
headstones.  Abel Galland is buried here along with his wife, Amy.  Abel lead the community
that resided near this location.
